14
00:03:17,923 --> 00:03:22,426
So, just a potted history of the Buddha's own life.

15
00:03:24,509 --> 00:03:26,972
Something happened in his twenties, mid-twenties,

16
00:03:27,373 --> 00:03:30,519
which we would call sort of an identity crisis.

17
00:03:31,621 --> 00:03:48,027
And it comes out in a little story about him going out on his hunting trips and whatnot and coming across these four figures, a very sick person, a very elderly person, a corpse, and then this ascetic sitting under a tree.

18
00:03:49,610 --> 00:03:54,157
So these are now known as the messengers from the gods that awoke into his path.

19
00:03:54,778 --> 00:04:19,875
but basically it was him coming to terms with the fact that youth was disappearing and ahead of him looked pretty miserable and in those days the idea of rebirth the idea of being reincarnated is not quite the same as rebirth but the idea of an ongoing process was was looked upon as horrific everybody's trying to get out of that I mean life wasn't so easy

20
00:04:20,310 --> 00:04:27,783
especially depending on which caste you were born in, although the castes at that time weren't so set, you could move.

21
00:04:29,504 --> 00:04:40,822
But the idea that you'd have to come back and do the same thing over and over again without any escape presented those times with their real existential suffering.

22
00:04:41,043 --> 00:04:41,944
How do you get out of that?

23
00:04:44,528 --> 00:04:47,213
And there were various teachers at that time,

24
00:04:47,512 --> 00:04:50,778
