26
00:04:53,601 --> 00:04:55,425
You basically died and that was the end of that.

27
00:04:56,607 --> 00:04:59,430
And the idea was you got the best out of life that you could.

28
00:05:00,213 --> 00:05:02,435
And that's all you could do really.

29
00:05:03,076 --> 00:05:07,923
So their idea of a good life was to get yourself as happy as you can.

30
00:05:07,944 --> 00:05:11,810
Mainly through the sensual delights of life.

31
00:05:12,651 --> 00:05:14,394
And that was it.

32
00:05:14,714 --> 00:05:16,137
And then you disappeared.

33
00:05:16,994 --> 00:05:27,406
There were others who had the idea, which is very close to our Western idea of a soul or a self, which is everlasting.

34
00:05:28,427 --> 00:05:35,737
And so, for instance, a contemporary teacher of the Buddha was the Jain founder, the Nigantha.

35
00:05:36,458 --> 00:05:44,266
So they seem to have had a very sort of concrete idea of what karma was, in other words, the consequence of your actions, your ethical actions.

36
00:05:45,074 --> 00:05:48,899
It was almost something material that got stuck on the soul.

37
00:05:49,680 --> 00:06:01,697
And the idea was that you went through mortification exercises so that this stuff fell off and then the soul could rise to a different place.

38
00:06:03,139 --> 00:06:12,673
And that's why they, and their understanding was that whatever you did, whether you meant it or not, if it wasn't good, you got the karmic result.

39
00:06:12,692 --> 00:06:13,713
So that's why you see

40
00:06:14,267 --> 00:06:16,971
You know, jain monks going around sweeping the floor in front of them.

41
00:06:18,093 --> 00:06:22,497
If they stand on an ant, whether they meant to or not is immaterial.

42
00:06:22,538 --> 00:06:24,860
They've killed that life and therefore there's a consequence.

43
00:06:25,762 --> 00:06:33,851
So, there was that teaching of self-mortification, of letting go of the appetite to the body.

44
00:06:34,252 --> 00:06:38,418
And that was mainly around sex, but a lot of it was around food.

45
00:06:38,718 --> 00:06:41,641
And the Buddha seems to have practiced this for quite some years.

46
00:06:42,466 --> 00:06:45,007
to the point where he said he could hold his spine through his stomach.

47
00:06:46,750 --> 00:06:48,211
